content: <?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?> <metadata> <idinfo> <citation> <citeinfo> <origin>USDA-FSA-APFO Aerial Photography Field Office</origin> <pubdate>20130801</pubdate> <title>The National Agriculture Imagery Program Change 2002-2013</title> <pubinfo> <pubplace>Salt Lake City, Utah</pubplace> <publish>USDA-FSA-APFO Aerial Photography Field Office</publish> </pubinfo> <onlink>http://usdaonline.maps.arcgis.com/apps/MapTour/index.html?appid=445e3dfd16c4401f95f78ad5905a4cce&webmap=6d117f2ede424ace93917e2bc88202b3</onlink> </citeinfo> </citation> <descript> <abstract>The National Agriculture Imagery Program Change 2002-2013 is a web mapping application hosted on the ArcGIS online FSA Organizational Subscription.  This web application is based on the hosted ArcGIS Online map tour template.  The application depicts NAIP imagery coverage starting in 2002 and ending in 2013.  The information contained in the JPEG images contained in the tour was aquired from historical archives of imagery coverage at the Aerial Photography Field Office.  Notation of change and highlights for each year was also derived from historical contracting sources at the Aerial Photography Field Office.</abstract> <purpose>To preserve the history of the National Agriculture Imagery Program and to educate the general public and NAIP imagery users about the history of the program and how it has changed over time.</purpose> </descript> <timeperd> <timeinfo> <sngdate> <caldate>2013</caldate> </sngdate> </timeinfo> <current>2013</current> </timeperd> <status> <progress>Complete</progress> <update>Yearly</update> </status> <spdom> <bounding> <westbc>-101.64</westbc> <eastbc>-101.61</eastbc> <northbc>40.53</northbc> <southbc>40.51</southbc> </bounding> </spdom> <keywords> <theme> <themekt>None</themekt> <themekey>farming</themekey> <themekey>NAIP</themekey> <themekey>Web Application</themekey> <themekey>Image</themekey> <themekey>Map Tour</themekey> <themekey>Change</themekey> <themekey>Historical</themekey> <themekey>Dates</themekey> <themekey>Aerial</themekey> <themekey>Aerial Photography</themekey> <themekey>Story Map</themekey> </theme> <place> <placekt>Geographic Names Information System</placekt> <placekey>"United States"</placekey> <placekey>US</placekey> <placekey>North America</placekey> <placekey>State</placekey> </place> </keywords> <accconst>None</accconst> <useconst> The map is for illustrative purposes only.
